# navigation.rules.mdc

### A. Purpose
Define consistent navigation architecture using Syncfusion UI Kit — Material-3 Theme components exclusively.

### B. Rules

**Architecture:**
- Primary navigation: `SfSidebar` (right side, RTL-first)
- Secondary in-section navigation: `SfTab`
- Breadcrumb: `SfBreadcrumb` — mandatory on all pages > one level deep
- App Bar: `SfAppBar` — fixed top, always visible
- Context actions: `SfToolbar` above content area — not in App Bar
- Sequential flows: `SfStepper`
- Hierarchical data navigation: `SfTreeView`

**SfSidebar Rules:**
- Three states: Expanded (with labels) / Collapsed (icons only) / Hidden (mobile drawer)
- Expanded width: 240px. Collapsed width: 64px.
- Use `SfSidebar` with `type='Push'` (desktop) / `type='Over'` (mobile)
- `enableRtl={true}` positions sidebar on right automatically
- Max two navigation levels. Third level uses sub-page or `SfTab`.
- Group items under section headers: 8px between items, 16px between groups
- Active item: `--color-sf-primary-container` bg + `--color-sf-on-primary-container` text (Material-3 handles)
- Badge counts on sidebar items: use `SfBadge`
- Icons mandatory for all items — `SfSidebar` supports icon + label per item

**SfAppBar Rules:**
- Height: 56px fixed — use `SfAppBar` component
- Always visible — `position='Top'` + sticky
- RTL: logo/product name at far right, user profile at far left (automatic with `enableRtl`)
- Global search: `SfAutoComplete` in AppBar center
- Notifications: icon button + `SfBadge` for unread count
- User profile: `SfAvatar` + `SfDropDownButton`

**SfTab Rules:**
- Use for parallel content sections — not sequential steps (use `SfStepper` for steps)
- Max 6 tabs — overflow handled by `SfTab` scroll mode
- Active tab: `--color-sf-primary` underline, 2px (Material-3 theme handles)
- Tab width: auto content-based, min 80px, max 160px
- Keyboard: Arrow Left/Right navigation built into `SfTab` with RTL awareness

**SfBreadcrumb Rules:**
- Place below `SfAppBar`, above page title
- Last item = current page (not a link) — use `disabled` on last item
- Max 4 levels — `SfBreadcrumb` handles overflow with `maxItems` prop
- RTL separator handled automatically with `enableRtl`

**Other Component Rules:**
- `SfAccordion` → expandable content groups in side panels, settings — NOT primary navigation
- `SfContextMenu` → row-level / element-level quick actions only
- `SfMenu` → application-level menu systems (document editors, complex tools)
- `SfTreeView` → hierarchical data navigation (file systems, org charts, categories)
- `SfStepper` → sequential multi-step workflows only — never for parallel content
- `SfCarousel` → content presentation only — never navigation

**RTL:**
- All Syncfusion navigation components respect `enableRtl(true)` globally.
- Do not manually mirror navigation layouts.

**Accessibility:**
- `SfSidebar` includes `role="navigation"` by default.
- `SfBreadcrumb` uses `aria-label="breadcrumb"` and `aria-current="page"` automatically.
- `SfTab` keyboard navigation (Arrow keys, Tab, Enter) is built in.
- Skip navigation link: add manually at page top for keyboard users.

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- ✅ Use `SfSidebar` as primary navigation on all enterprise screens.
- ✅ Use `SfTab` for switching between parallel views.
- ✅ Show `SfBreadcrumb` on all pages below root level.
- ✅ Use `SfStepper` for sequential workflows.
- ✅ Collapse `SfSidebar` to icon-only on tablet via `isOpen` prop control.

**Don't:**
- ❌ Do not use > 2 navigation levels in `SfSidebar`.
- ❌ Do not use `SfAccordion` as primary navigation.
- ❌ Do not mix `SfTab` and `SfStepper` for the same pattern.
- ❌ Do not place action buttons in `SfAppBar` — use `SfToolbar`.
- ❌ Do not use `SfCarousel` for section navigation.
- ❌ Do not manually style navigation components — use Material-3 theme tokens.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating a new application screen, auto-generate: `SfSidebar` (right, RTL), `SfAppBar` (top, fixed), content area.
- When generating multi-section content, auto-add `SfTab` at top of content zone.
- When generating hierarchical navigation, use `SfTreeView` inside `SfSidebar`.
- When generating multi-step flows, auto-select `SfStepper`.
- When generating AppBar: product name (right), `SfAutoComplete` search (center), notification + `SfAvatar` (left) for RTL.
- All Syncfusion navigation components: pass `enableRtl={true}` prop or rely on global `enableRtl(true)` bootstrap.
